  <entry>
    <title>Some issues and their solutions about coursera</title>
    <link href="http://yoursite.com/2018/09/22/Some-issues-and-their-solutions-about-coursera/"/>
    <id>http://yoursite.com/2018/09/22/Some-issues-and-their-solutions-about-coursera/</id>
    <published>2018-09-22T00:38:40.000Z</published>
    <updated>2018-09-22T01:10:11.737Z</updated>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<link rel="stylesheet" class="aplayer-secondary-style-marker" href="\assets\css\APlayer.min.css"><script src="\assets\js\APlayer.min.js" class="aplayer-secondary-script-marker"></script><script class="meting-secondary-script-marker" src="\assets\js\Meting.min.js"></script><p>Coursera is one of the most famous online learning platforms. However, some frustrating things could occur either, here are some issues I met and the solutions of them.</p><h4 id="Problem1-the-video-is-loading-all-the-time"><a href="#Problem1-the-video-is-loading-all-the-time" class="headerlink" title="Problem1: the video is loading all the time:"></a>Problem1: the video is loading all the time:</h4><h5 id="method"><a href="#method" class="headerlink" title="method:"></a>method:</h5><p>open your <code>hosts</code> file, for most windows users, it’s in <code>C:\Windows\System32\drivers\etc</code></p><p>add these lines to the bottom of your hosts file and save it</p><figure class="highlight plain"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br><span class="line">8</span><br><span class="line">9</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">52.84.246.90    d3c33hcgiwev3.cloudfront.net</span><br><span class="line">52.84.246.252    d3c33hcgiwev3.cloudfront.net</span><br><span class="line">52.84.246.144    d3c33hcgiwev3.cloudfront.net</span><br><span class="line">52.84.246.72    d3c33hcgiwev3.cloudfront.net</span><br><span class="line">52.84.246.106    d3c33hcgiwev3.cloudfront.net</span><br><span class="line">52.84.246.135    d3c33hcgiwev3.cloudfront.net</span><br><span class="line">52.84.246.114    d3c33hcgiwev3.cloudfront.net</span><br><span class="line">52.84.246.90    d3c33hcgiwev3.cloudfront.net</span><br><span class="line">52.84.246.227    d3c33hcgiwev3.cloudfront.net</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>run cmd.exe, input <code>ipconfig/flushdns</code> then press <code>Enter</code></p><p>refresh your coursera page, the video will play out successfully.</p><p><br></p><h4 id="Problem2-the-subtitles-are-too-big-small"><a href="#Problem2-the-subtitles-are-too-big-small" class="headerlink" title="Problem2: the subtitles are too big/small"></a>Problem2: the subtitles are too big/small</h4><h5 id="method-1"><a href="#method-1" class="headerlink" title="method:"></a>method:</h5><p>inspect the page(by right click to choose or press F12), add <code>video::-webkit-media-text-track-display {font-size: xx%;}</code> to head-&gt;<code>&lt;style class=&quot;vjs-styles-defaults&gt;&quot;</code> just like this:<br><br><br><img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/dbmkzs2ez/image/upload/v1537606039/coursera_1.png" alt="untitle"></p><p>(you can change the percentage value to find your perfect subtitle size)</p><p>to be continued…</p>]]></content>
    
